  "response": "As an Indian passport holder, you can travel to several countries without a visa or with a visa on arrival. Some of these countries include:\n\nVisa-free or Visa on Arrival:\n1. Nepal\n2. Bhutan\n3. Sri Lanka\n4. Cambodia\n5. Indonesia\n6. Maldives\n7. Thailand (for tourism)\n8. Timor-Leste\n9. Jamaica\n10. Mauritius\n\nRelatively Easy Visa Process:\n1. Iran\n2. Azerbaijan\n3. Bolivia\n4. Kazakhstan\n5. Kenya\n6. Singapore (with prior e-visa)\n7. Vietnam (e-visa)\n\nNote: Visa requirements can change frequently, so it's always recommended to:\n- Check the latest visa requirements before traveling\n- Verify entry conditions with the respective country's embassy\n- Ensure your passport is valid for at least 6 months beyond your travel dates\n- Have sufficient funds and return ticket\n- Confirm any COVID-19 related travel restrictions\n\nFor the most up-to-date and accurate information, consult official government websites or contact the respective country's embassy.",
